reviews.review_text: all shows are 5 stars on it tonight!
One hell of a good night!! I'll try to keep it brief but God Damn if this wasn't one of those nights where you rang that bell turn night to day.  Ring like fire.  Keep the Faith Brothers and Sisters!

Hark the Raven.... I love this show.When I first started collecting tapes in the early 80s,this was one of my first loves.Wore that tape out.Was one of the ones I would grab to turn someone on.Loved to freak people out with the raven space.TRIPPY.A solid show start to finish.Nothing negative to say.Favorite of mine from 82'Sound quality is very good!Give it a whirl!!

False advertising! Hey, man! I thought from the list and comments I was gonna really hear some Poe: maybe read by Ken Nordine, or at least some Cassidyesque variations on the theme by Kesey or somebody. Instead I get a bunch of grab-assing gas-heads flashing back to the Anthem of the Sun studio sessions. Still, interesting Space anyway. 

First set is mixed, partly awesome.

Really beautiful Stella, but mostly the second set is pretty rough-to-average.
